news.title: China's Sino-Ocean enters deal to restructure $5.6 billion offshore debt
news.para: The Beijing-based company will issue a new U.S. dollar-denominated term loan facility and notes worth $2.2 billion to its creditors, according to the proposal.

news.title: China to hasten restructuring work model for real estate industry
news.para: It is necessary to establish a basic system of financing, taxation and land sales compatible with the development of real estate, the official, Han Wenxiu told a press conference in Beijing after a key party meet ended on Thursday.

news.title: London's Canary Wharf plans to reshape HSBC tower in overhaul
news.para: Qatar's sovereign wealth fund the Qatar Investment Authority (QIA), which owns the 45-floor building, and the area's landlord Canary Wharf Group (CWG), said they planned to reshape the tower to make it more suitable for a mix of uses.

news.title: UltraTech Cement reports net profit of Rs 1,696 crore in Q1 FY25
news.para: Its revenue from operations was up 1.87 per cent at Rs 18,069.56 crore during the period. It was at Rs 17,737.10 crore in the corresponding period a year ago.

news.title: Aadhar Housing Finance expects 20% increase in disbursement
news.para: Rishi Anand, MD and CEO of the company said that it has requested the government to redefine income criteria of economically weaker section (EWS) to Rs 5 lakh and low income group (LIG) to Rs 10 lakh.

news.title: Sales of construction equipment remains flat in Q1 FY25
news.para: Senior industry executives estimate sales of construction equipment, widely regarded as a barometer of economic activity, to remain sluggish this year.

news.title: Bengaluru: Residents in White Rose Layout face poor road conditions
news.para: Approximately 50 families living in White Rose Layout near Hope Farm Junction, Whitefield, within the Mahadevapura Assembly constituency, are facing significant issues due to inadequate road infrastructure.

news.title: Havells India's net profit up 43.08% in Q1 FY25
news.para: Havells India's net consolidated total income stood at Rs 5,875.14 crore in Q1 FY25, a growth of 20.19 per cent from Rs 4,888.39 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: Dalmia Bharat's net profit up 0.69% in Q1 FY25
news.para: Dalmia Bharat's net consolidated total income stood at Rs 3,671 crore in Q1 FY25, a minor dip of 0.27 per cent from Rs 3,681 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: Promoters must publish project QR codes in every brochure & advertisement: UP-RERA
news.para: Buyers can scan this code to get all the details of the project from the portal of UP-RERA and verify the information about the projects provided by the promoter in the advertisements.

news.title: ASK Property Fund invests Rs 190 crore in Kalpataru project
news.para: The project is an upper mid-segment project, located in Borivali West, comprising 310 units and is spread across six acres with a total saleable area of about 6.5 lakh sq ft.

news.title: COWRKS leases four new centres in Mumbai & Bengaluru
news.para: This expansion will add 1.4 lakh sq ft, increasing COWRKS' total presence to 15 lakh sq ft across 34 operational centres.

news.title: RLDA invites bids for leasing of 5,532 sq meters of commercial land in Andhra Pradesh
news.para: The proposed land parcel near Renigunta Junction Railway Station will be leased out for 45 years. The reserve price of the land is Rs 6.77 crore for a proposed built-up area of 7,502 sq meters.

news.title: Building permits for apartments in Germany fall by 24% in May 2024
news.para: Germany's property sector, in its third year of decline, is undergoing its most severe slump in decades. Permits are an important indicator of future construction activity.

news.title: ThaiBev to transfer entire stake in Frasers Property to TCC Assets
news.para: The drink maker, controlled by Thai billionaire Charoen Sirivadhanabhakdi, said its unit InterBev Investment would transfer its 28.78% stake in Frasers Property to Thailand-based TCC Assets.

news.title: South Korea’s finance minister vows to take policy steps to stabilize rising house prices
news.para: "Volatility is increasing in the real estate market recently, with apartment prices rising more sharply in Seoul and the wider capital area," Finance Minister Choi Sang-mok said during a policy meeting with the land minister.

news.title: Single-family housing starts in USA fall 2.2% in June
news.para: That is keeping home prices elevated and combining with higher borrowing costs to push homeownership, long viewed as the American dream, out of the reach of many.

news.title: Andhra Pradesh CM warns ministers to not interfere in sand mining
news.para: After the cabinet meeting was over, Naidu spoke to the ministers on a few issues. He said that the free sand policy should be implemented in a transparent manner and there should not be any political interference either by the ministers or by the MLAs.

news.title: Bombay HC orders seven members in way of society redevelopment to vacate or pay Rs 5 lakh
news.para: DEM Homes LLP had filed a commercial arbitration petition to adjudicate the dispute between it and the dissenting members. In Sept 2023, a redevelopment agreement was executed between the developer and Taruvel CHSL.

news.title: Tamil Nadu government handed over free pattas to 6.52 lakh poor since 2021
news.para: Highlighting the achievements in the rural development and panchayat raj department in the last three years, an official release said the DMK govt allocated Rs 5,337 crore towards old age pension.
